All.name: jishaku repeat
All.help:
Runs a command multiple times in a row.

This acts like the command was invoked several times manually, so it obeys cooldowns.
You can use this in conjunction with `jsk sudo` to bypass this.

All.name: jishaku retain
All.help:
Turn variable retention for REPL on or off.

Provide no argument for current status.

All.name: jishaku curl
All.help:
Download and display a text file from the internet.

This command is similar to jsk cat, but accepts a URL.

All.name: jishaku ast
All.help: Disassemble Python code into AST.

All.name: jishaku node
All.help: Shortcut for scaffolding and executing 'npm run'. Only exists if the executables are detected.

All.name: jishaku cancel
All.help:
Cancels a task with the given index.

If the index passed is -1, will cancel the last task instead.

All.name: jishaku override
All.help:
Run a command with a different user, channel, or thread, optionally bypassing checks and cooldowns.

Users will try to resolve to a Member, but will use a User if it can't find one.

All.name: jishaku debug
All.help: Run a command timing execution and catching exceptions.

All.name: jishaku py
All.help: Direct evaluation of Python code.

All.name: jishaku permtrace
All.help:
Calculates the source of granted or rejected permissions.

This accepts a channel, and either a member or a list of roles.
It calculates permissions the same way Discord does, while keeping track of the source.

All.name: jishaku voice
All.help:
Voice-related commands.

If invoked without subcommand, relays current voice state.

All.name: jishaku shell
All.help:
Executes statements in the system shell.

This uses the system shell as defined in $SHELL, or `/bin/bash` otherwise.
Execution can be cancelled by closing the paginator.

All.name: jishaku rustc
All.help: Shortcut for scaffolding and executing 'cargo run'. Only exists if the executables are detected.

All.name: jishaku source
All.help: Displays the source code for a command.

All.name: jishaku rtt
All.help: Calculates Round-Trip Time to the API.

All.name: jishaku load
All.help:
Loads or reloads the given extension names.

Reports any extensions that failed to load.

All.name: jishaku hide
All.help: Hides Jishaku from the help command.

All.name: jishaku invite
All.help:
Retrieve the invite URL for this bot.

If the names of permissions are provided, they are requested as part of the invite.

All.name: jishaku py_inspect
All.help: Evaluation of Python code with inspect information.

All.name: jishaku git
All.help: Shortcut for 'jsk sh git'. Invokes the system shell.

All.name: jishaku unload
All.help:
Unloads the given extension names.

Reports any extensions that failed to unload.

Jishaku.name: jishaku repeat

Runs a command multiple times in a row.

This acts like the command was invoked several times manually, so it obeys cooldowns.
You can use this in conjunction with `jsk sudo` to bypass this.

Turn variable retention for REPL on or off.

Provide no argument for current status.

Jishaku.name: jishaku cancel
Jishaku.help:
Cancels a task with the given index.

If the index passed is -1, will cancel the last task instead.

Jishaku.name: jishaku override
Jishaku.help:
Run a command with a different user, channel, or thread, optionally bypassing checks and cooldowns.

Users will try to resolve to a Member, but will use a User if it can't find one.

Jishaku.name: jishaku debug
Jishaku.help: Run a command timing execution and catching exceptions.

Jishaku.name: jishaku py

Jishaku.name: jishaku permtrace
Jishaku.help:
Calculates the source of granted or rejected permissions.

This accepts a channel, and either a member or a list of roles.
It calculates permissions the same way Discord does, while keeping track of the source.

Jishaku.name: jishaku voice
Jishaku.help:
Voice-related commands.

If invoked without subcommand, relays current voice state.

Jishaku.name: jishaku shell
Jishaku.help:
Executes statements in the system shell.

This uses the system shell as defined in $SHELL, or `/bin/bash` otherwise.
Execution can be cancelled by closing the paginator.

Jishaku.name: jishaku rtt
Jishaku.help: Calculates Round-Trip Time to the API.
